External Job Title Gerente de Segurança

Function Corporate Security
Type of Job Full Time - Exempt
Country Brazil
External Job Description 
Context:

·  Test Company is the world's leading premium drinks business with an outstanding collection of beveragealcohol brands across the spirits, wine and beer categories. These brands include Johnnie Walker, Smirnoff, Guinness and Baileys.

·  Corporate Security sits within the Group Legal function and the Global Director of Corporate Security reports directly to the General Counsel.

·  Corporate Security's mission is to protect Test Company's people, assets, brands and future growth through setting policies and standards and monitoring their implementation, by providing expert guidance and services.



Leadership Responsibilities:

·  Proactively provide commercial and pragmatic security advice and solutions for the Markets, including working with the Corporate Security team globally to set policy and standards and manage security programs;

·  To work with the businesses and other internal stakeholders such as the HR, Legal and Corporate Relations teams on relevant matters affecting the Markets, including counterfeit issues;

·  Carry out independent internal investigations as directed;

·  To build up an effective internal and external network of contacts to assist with the protection of the Test Company business .



Purpose of Role:

Will be responsible for:


* 
Having a comprehensive understanding of all the businesses within the region and the risks they face; 
* 
Communicating the risks to the regional executive and providing appropriate advice; 
* 
Ensuring the physical security of all facilities and personnel in the PUB Region, including conducting security vulnerability assessments; 
* 
Conducting and managing internal and external investigations in conjunction with other business functions and law enforcement authorities; 
* 
Preparing high quality reports including intelligence briefings, threats assessments and investigative reports; 
* 
Overseeing the budget. 
* 
Contributing to the global response to crises (CMT); 
* 
Establishing and maintaining close liaison with relevant law enforcement and government officials and facilitating training and security awareness for employees.


Top 3-5 Accountabilies


* 
Ensure all Test Company sites, and relevant third party sites, including event sites, in the region are compliant with Test Company policies and standards and other regulatory requirements; 
* 
Driving proactive programs to mitigate current and emerging risks and trends; 
* 
Conducting Investigations as required by the Global Director of Corporate Security and the PUB GM; 
* 
Building and maintaining effective contacts in relevant Law Enforcement, Regulatory and Industry bodies; 
* 
Delivering high quality, forward looking briefing papers and threat assessments.


Qualifications and Experience Required:

· Good knowledge of the commercial security field including, experience in threat analysis and developing risk analysis; experience in evaluating and implementing physical asset protection and conducting site surveys; awareness of executive protection and event security; conducting and managing complex investigations, i.e. fraud allegations and civil investigations; conducting witness, victim, and suspect interviews’ experience; information security knowledge and experience

·  Excellent interpersonal and communication skills;

·  Good commercial and pragmatic approach;

·  Be able to prepare documentation for corporate leadership or governmental agencies;

·Verbal and written proficiency in English and Portuguese required; Spanish is recommended and would be a bonus;

·  Ability to stay focused by constantly reassessing priorities within the business;

·  Ability to work confidently, persuasively and to gain the respect and trust of other senior managers;

·  Flexible attitude to travel;

·  International experience – prior living or working in more than one country would be useful;

·Bachelor’s degree required; a Law or Masters degree or other advanced degree would be beneficial;

 Prior experience is required in law enforcement or as   a corporate security professional

